OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: George
OL,4,CChandler
OL,6,FHe said: "I was a gunner. It was half
OL,7,Fpast four in the morning when the
OL,8,Fskipper told the crew to make ready
OL,9,Ffor sea and overhead were planes of
OL,10,Fall sizes and types heading for the
OL,11,FFrench coast.
OL,13,F"We kept to the coast because we were
OL,14,Fon guard against German E-boats.
OL,16,F"If you like, they were German motor
OL,17,Ftorpedo boats - we couldn't go inland
OL,18,Fbecause we were guarding against
OL,19,FGerman forces coming round the coast.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/5
